You always call your `numb` method with one argument: the first one is defined, the next ones are not ; hence the `undefined` error. You should change your method like this:

```ts
numb(button) {
  this.thread.push(button.value);
}
```

You can also directly call your method with the right value instead of passing by the `value` parameter, and so you can avoid the `#` syntax:

```html
&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; (click)=&#39;numb(1)&#39;&gt;1&lt;/button&gt;
```

```ts
numb(value) {
  this.thread.push(value);
}
```

